  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a wok over medium-high heat.",
    "Add garlic and sauté for about 30 seconds until fragrant.",
    "Toss in the diced red potatoes, salt, black pepper, and lemon juice.",
    "Pour in the broth and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for about 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.",
    "Add honey (if using) halfway through cooking time and stir well to prevent burning.",
    "Serve hot as a side dish with grilled chicken or steak."
